contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|overboard}} '''Overboard''' may refer to: Going or flying off a ship or boat into water *[[Man overboard]]; a situation where a person goes over the side of a ship or boat into the water, possibly needing rescue *[[Overboard (film)|''Overboard'' (1987 film)]], a 1987 movie starring Goldie Hawn and Kurt Russell *[[Overboard (comic strip)|''Overboard'' (comic strip)]], a comic strip about a group of pirates *''[[Overboard!]]'', a 1997 video game published by Psygnosis *[[Overboard (a cappella)]], an all-male ''a cappella'' group from New England *''[[Going Overboard]]'', a 1989 film starring Adam Sandler * ''[[Overboard & Down]]'', a 2006 EP by indie band Okkervil River * ''[[Saint Overboard]]'', a 1936 mystery novel by Leslie Charteris * ''[[Boy Overboard]]'', a 2004 novel by Morris Gleitzman * [[Going Overboard (album)|''Going Overboard'' (album)]], a 2007 album by Bounding Main {{disambig}}
